edu.purdue.cs59000.umltranslator.umlcontainer

Class UMLAlternatives

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.purdue.cs59000.umltranslator.UMLSymbol
      • edu.purdue.cs59000.umltranslator.umlcontainer.UMLContainer
        • edu.purdue.cs59000.umltranslator.umlcontainer.UMLAlternatives
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HasCodeHandler, HasSource, HasChildContainer, HasParentContainer, java.io.Serializable

    public class UMLAlternatives
extends UMLContainer
    UMLAlternatives defines an if-else statement. It holds references to a UMLCondition (if) and a UMLElse (else) and also defines their parent-child relationships upon setting. The child container of a UMLAlternative will be its UMLCondition.
    Author:
    Steve Yarusinsky
